defaultNatural Environment Research Council (
defaultNERC
default) and is its principal supplier of national capability in geoscience.
default 
defaultIt advances understanding of the structure, 
defaultproperties
default and processes of the solid Earth system through interdisciplinary surveys, monitoring and research for the benefit of society. 
defaultThe BGS
default is the UK's premier provider of objective and authoritative geoscientific data, information and knowledge for 
defaultwealth creation, sustainable use of natural resources, reducing risk and living with the impacts of environmental change. 
defaultWe are a world-leading geoscience centre for:
defaultMineralsUK
default is the 
defaultBritish Geological Survey (BGS)
default Centre for Sustainable Mineral Development. Facilitated by the BGS Minerals and Waste science programme, the Centre is a 
defaultglobal leader in the compilation, provision and analysis of mineral statistics and the major UK national provider of spatial and statistical minerals information. We also carry out research in areas directly relevant to our user community, such as metallog
defaultenesis, land-use impacts of mineral extraction and geomaterials.
