default6. Is there sufficient defaultengagement between UK extractive industries and the NGO sector? Are there examples of best practice in engagement between the extractive industries and NGOs?default&#xa0;
defaultAt the national level the UK Minerals Forum facilitates regular and structured dialogue between i
defaultndustry, regulators, policy makers and NGOs. UKMF is 
defaultvaluable
default in debating contentious topics and identifying key issues relating to sustainable development of UK mineral resources. For example, the UKMF is currently undertaking a forty year horizon scan on
default the future of UK mineral extraction. The BGS is a founder member of the UKMF.
default&#xa0;
defaultOutside of the UKMF our experience is that the larger NGOs do have an understanding of minerals related issues. However, across the sector many 
defaultother 
defaultgroups find the technical aspects of mineral development challenging. The BGS has an important role to play in helping NGOs and the wider community understand the economic, social and environmental issues related to mineral development. For example, see ou
defaultr Mineral Planning 
defaultFactsheets
